========================================
Installing ONIE on Extreme Networks X870
========================================

Cross-Compiling ONIE
====================

Change directories to ``build-config`` to compile ONIE.

To compile ONIE first change directories to ``build-config`` and then
type ``"make MACHINEROOT=../machine/extremenetworks  MACHINE=extremenetworks_x870 all"``.
For example::

  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINEROOT=../machine/extremenetworks  MACHINE=extremenetworks_x870 all

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in
``build/images``::

-rw-r--r-- 1 will SD1  5527152 Mar  7 11:18 extremenetworks_x870-r1.initrd
-rw-r--r-- 1 will SD1  3093248 Mar  7 11:18 extremenetworks_x870-r1.vmlinuz
-rw-r--r-- 1 will SD1 19857408 Mar  7 11:19 onie-recovery-x86_64-extremenetworks_x870-r1.iso
-rw-r--r-- 1 will SD1  8675191 Mar  7 11:19 onie-updater-x86_64-extremenetworks_x870-r1

extremenetworks_x870-r1.vmlinuz -- This is the ONIE kernel image

extremenetworks_x870-r1.initrd  -- This is the ONIE initramfs (filesystem)

onie-updater-x86_64-extremenetworks_x870-r1 -- This is the ONIE self-update
image.  This image is a self-extracting archive used for installing ONIE.
